& my last to you was on the 30 past to which referre you, sence recd yd, of
22 ditto, the yacht is dispaited the 30 past & sence well arrived in Englands
so thate am sorry ian not comply nith yd order, & am sure the lares
will prove well, for am vere well accquainted in that trade & have large
commissions from those, that have been served by others here before, & do not
guestion, butt when you have them with you butt that you will finde a
good acctt: and according what you hence forward shall order, shall endeavor
to incorridge you, for never gelt have sent a tryal of laces in to england,
butt then I found mereafing orders & continuany if you please to have any
guid leather hangings, or pictures & can serve you in boath, principally
in nictures, which wee tould up & make in a bite litt le bon & may be must
a side well, enough our binlanders can bring that in butt the guldid leathes
must have some other directions the autt of the al monos is sent so om
hartolj & thert of the garne shall be sent you pr fiest whilst remaine

S in answerts god of 18t past as to the bale of tykes I can not ellon
abatement, oneles would allon mee abatements upon the cloathes sold
for the same, for I am foried to putt them of so because I can not
sat stay any other mony custome nith yd cloathes so you east do the best
you can with the tykes, as I must to nith the closses there beeng yet
7 resting though I have been at the charge of repressing & toillettioy
I have sent many houndred tykes in to England, & if any sever
sended cheaper Ill loose a whole bale, there fore you are not well
inforneed that others can afferd them cheaper in london I do all
I can to pust of these resting goods, for I would fame mah and
end to y beeng more desireous to clcare itt, then you van be for
to have valeu as soone as possible shall send you the cmtt & remise
which is the needfull as present from
London Abram Vivian

my last to you was on the pm curtt. sence recd yd of 22th past new troubles againe
you contradicted the shipping of the bayes I say the ceary bayes for lotterdam
which i tock affect will be great preiudice, for I want the leary bayes, beeng
att a great loss for them. in mine of the 18:2 past I sayd, that I fuspected the
trath of the goods beeng shipped, butt did not contradict them bayes, for I want
them to muy, I thought marmadih smish should have been gon, & arrived
before now att Rotterdam butt no news, less mee have good store of bayes
of about 35 a 40 ƒ though 50 a 60 without what I ordered before
avery bett ready for Bindard: pray be qich a gepedient for mony for
mij acctt you may draw 2 a 300 ½ more, though I have sae some ready, but
